{"id":"math120-defint210-app002","cid":"MATH 120","topic":"Applications of Integration","subtopic":"Total accumulated change","difficulty":2,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"A factory's output rate is O(t) = x^{n} (hundreds of units/hour). Find the total output over hours {lo} to {hi}.","params":{"a":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":1},"n":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":2},"lo":{"type":"int","min":0,"max":2},"hi":{"type":"int","min":3,"max":6}},"answer_expr":"defint210","steps":["Total = integral from {lo} to {hi} of x^{n} dx = [x^{n+1}/({n+1})] from {lo} to {hi}.","= ({hi_pow} - {lo_pow}) / ({n+1}) = {answer_defint210} hundred units."],"tags":["survey-calculus","applications","total-output","production"]}
